LMMS sounds exported in Linux are scratchy
It seems to only affect the FreeBoy plugin's sounds, and only on Linux
For now, I've kept the original sound data files generated in Windows LMMS and set the build system to not
rebuild sound files

The Google Play Games SDK is currently only supported on Android NDK r10e
The engine is now being built with a newer NDK, so I've disabled Google Play Games SDK support for the time being
If and when Google gets around to making the Google Play Games SDK compatible with newer NDK versions, re-enable
Google Play Games SDK support

In Desktop mode, fullscreen, 1280x720, the small font looks terrible
This seems to be true in other modes as well
